                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/5287: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-05T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >November 5, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 5—1:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>50. The International Financial Commission informs me that in consequence of
                    information received from the Greek Government, it regards itself as authorized
                    to suspend payment of amounts due <pb facs="0328" n="214" xml:id="pg_214"/> the
                    United States on November 10, 1931 and May 10, 1932 in consequence of the
                    applicability of the President’s moratorium program.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
